<article id="post-2507" class="post-2507 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-community-management category-startups category-tech category-video">
	<div class="blog-item-wrap">
				<a href="http://talkweb.eu/bulgaria-web-summit-2014-with-github-elasticsearch-smashingmag-and-more-friends/" title="Bulgaria Web Summit 2014 with GitHub, ElasticSearch, SmashingMag and more friends" >
			 				</a>
		<div class="post-inner-content">
			<header class="entry-header page-header">

				<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://talkweb.eu/bulgaria-web-summit-2014-with-github-elasticsearch-smashingmag-and-more-friends/" rel="bookmark">Bulgaria Web Summit 2014 with GitHub, ElasticSearch, SmashingMag and more friends</a></h1>

								<div class="entry-meta">
					<span class="posted-on"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> <a href="http://talkweb.eu/bulgaria-web-summit-2014-with-github-elasticsearch-smashingmag-and-more-friends/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2014-02-21T17:18:01+00:00">February 21, 2014</time></a></span><span class="byline"> <i class="fa fa-user"></i> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://talkweb.eu/author/admin/">Bogomil Shopov</a></span></span>				<span class="comments-link"><i class="fa fa-comment-o"></i><a href="http://talkweb.eu/bulgaria-web-summit-2014-with-github-elasticsearch-smashingmag-and-more-friends/#respond" title="Comment on Bulgaria Web Summit 2014 with GitHub, ElasticSearch, SmashingMag and more friends">Leave a comment</a></span>
				
				
				</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
							</header><!-- .entry-header -->

						<div class="entry-content">

					<p dir="ltr">I think it&#8217;s time to write something about Bulgaria Web Summit &#8211; the event I am organizing since 2004. Of course the name back then was WebTech but this is just a formality.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Why Bulgaria Web Summit?</p>
<p dir="ltr">Honestly I don&#8217;t know, it was like &#8230; how we will name it .. Bulgaria Web Summit. The funny story is I talked 2 days ago with Florian from <a href="http://usersnap.com">Usersnap</a> and he asked me &#8220;I was wondering if <a href="https://twitter.com/paddycosgrave">Paddy Cosgrave</a> already sent  you an angry mail (about the name)&#8221; and today I&#8217;ve got a call from UK-ish number and I thought here it is, the angry Paddy is calling me.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let&#8217;s go back to the event. It will be amazing, as usual. We will have speakers and friends from <a href="http://github.com">GitHub</a>, <a href="http://www.elasticsearch.org/">ElasticSearch</a>, eCommera,<a href="http://smashingmagazine.com">Smashing Magazine</a> and even more and more. We will have of course a prime minister talking &#8230;well not the Bulgarian one, we don&#8217;t really like him, but the one from the Ministry of World Domination, no kidding.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Developer track</h2>
<p dir="ltr">In short: JavaScript, Development Workflows, ElasticSearch &amp;&amp; Python, Arduino, Raspberry Pi, Embedded Devices hacking and more</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Designer, UX, UI, VDT track</h2>
<p dir="ltr">Responsive Design , Visual Design Thinking, CSS, Fonts, UX and UI, Firefox OS</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Business track</h2>
<p dir="ltr">Product Ownership, Social media marketing, Kanban for Marketing, Showcase of successful products, Job fair and much more.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">3 rooms, 30 speakers and a party!</span></strong></p>
<h3>Danish Knan from GitHub is introducing his talk at Bulgaria Web summit in Sofia</h3>
<p><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/EUkFJR_Ird8?rel=0" height="480" width="853" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>

