<article id="post-2504" class="post-2504 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-closed-technologies category-itmarketing">
	<div class="blog-item-wrap">
				<a href="http://talkweb.eu/geeksphone-e-mail-campaign-is-not-for-geeks/" title="@Geeksphone e-mail campaign is &#8230;not for geeks" >
			 				</a>
		<div class="post-inner-content">
			<header class="entry-header page-header">

				<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://talkweb.eu/geeksphone-e-mail-campaign-is-not-for-geeks/" rel="bookmark">@Geeksphone e-mail campaign is &#8230;not for geeks</a></h1>

								<div class="entry-meta">
					<span class="posted-on"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> <a href="http://talkweb.eu/geeksphone-e-mail-campaign-is-not-for-geeks/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2014-02-21T12:53:25+00:00">February 21, 2014</time></a></span><span class="byline"> <i class="fa fa-user"></i> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://talkweb.eu/author/admin/">Bogomil Shopov</a></span></span>				<span class="comments-link"><i class="fa fa-comment-o"></i><a href="http://talkweb.eu/geeksphone-e-mail-campaign-is-not-for-geeks/#respond" title="Comment on @Geeksphone e-mail campaign is &#8230;not for geeks">Leave a comment</a></span>
				
				
				</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
							</header><!-- .entry-header -->

						<div class="entry-content">

					<p>I just opened an email from Geeksphone. They are trying to sell &#8220;Revolution&#8221;.  Revolution is not something you can sell, and it should not be something you should be able to buy &#8211; terrible name for an e-mail campaign subject. I&#8217;ve opened it just because I like Geeksphone products, but after that booom!</p>
<p>Yes it&#8217;s Revolution:</p>
<ul>
<li>No text on the visible part of my screen. Nada! I am not scrolling, sorry!</li>
<li> Of course alt =&#8221; &#8221; &lt;- this is so geeky  and it&#8217;s a standard now <img src="http://talkweb.eu/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" />  Who will need them, right.</li>
</ul>
<p>I will unsubscribe.</p>
<p><a href="http://talkweb.eu/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/geekphone.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2505" alt="geekphone" src="http://talkweb.eu/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/geekphone.png" width="962" height="627" /></a></p>

				<p><a class="btn btn-default read-more" href="http://talkweb.eu/geeksphone-e-mail-campaign-is-not-for-geeks/" title="@Geeksphone e-mail campaign is &#8230;not for geeks">Read More</a></p>

							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
					</div>
	</div>
